      "content": "<p>zyON,</p> <p>If your client needs to add additional brands, collections, types, then they will need access to those pages.</p> <p>To make it less confusing, you can set them up underneath a parent page.</p> <p><strong>Categories</strong></p> <p>-- Brands</p> <p>---- Brand 1</p> <p>---- Brand 2</p> <p>---- Brand 3</p> <p>-- Types</p> <p>---- Type A</p> <p>---- Type B</p> <p>---- Type C</p> <p>-- Collections</p> <p>---- Collection 1</p> <p>---- Collection 2</p> <p>---- Collection 3</p> <p>If you set the parent page /categories to hidden, then it will show as a lighter color in the page tree, and searches won't return any of those pages.</p> <p>I tend to use something like /tools/ or /config/ to keep things like this all grouped in one nice location.</p>",
